Netcode plugins are a powerful way to handle asymmetrical multiplayer plugins. It can allow clients to control the match, when normally only the host can. This is much better described in this video by CinderBlock
https://youtu.be/jyFuN8k2uIs&nbsp;
If you want to make your own netcode plugin, there&rsquo;s a template for it just like normal plugins. It does all the setup shown in the above video automatically. Follow the README to install it
https://github.com/ubelhj/BakkesmodNetcodePluginTemplate&nbsp;

